Once the model is trained on ATUS respondents, a synthetic person Pi, j is randomly assigned a survey individual from the leaf nodes in the trained ensemble model. Thus, the result gives every synthetic individual a time-use diary. The energy-use models will extract home activities from a time-diary and also build a household-level occupancy schedule over the 24-hour duration, denoted as ⟨Oi,0,Oi,1,…,Oi,23⟩\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
